extensionName.description: Please keep in mind that these strings had to be approved by the Google Brand Features Team. Be sure to make clear that this extension is *FOR* Google Calendar and not *BY* Google. Also, it was explicitly stated, that the phrase 'Google Calendar' should be localized just as it is on the localized versions of the Google Calendar UI.

gdata.migration.description.message: Penyedia Google Calendar telah mengesan bahawa anda ada kalendar yang hanya boleh mengakses Google Calendar dalam mod baca-sahaja. Jika anda ingin menaik taraf mana-mana kalendar, sila pilih di bawah.

gdata.wizard.session.description.message: Sila pilih sesi semasa atau masukkan alamat e-mel anda untuk mencipta sesi yang baru. Anda hanya perlukan satu sesi bagi setiap akaun.

gdata.wizard.calendars.description.message: Sila pilih senarai kalendar dan tugasan yang anda mahu langgan.

gdata.wizard.nextstep.description.message: Sila pergi ke langkah seterusnya untuk menetapkan kalendar anda.

busyTitle.description: Events with only free/busy access don't have a title, they will use this title instead. The calendar name is used as a parameter, since its often named after the person whose calendar you are viewing.

calendar_name.example: The name of the calendar, e.g. 'Home'

quotaExceeded.message: Kuota $session_id$ telah melebihi had, sila cuba lagi nanti.
quotaExceeded.description: This is shown when the request quota has been exceeded.

providerOutdated.message: Versi penyedia ini telah luput, sila kemaskini ke versi terkini.
